cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new method for training Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) that models them explicitly as finite games in mixed strategies. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, given that the paper focuses on improving the training of GANs, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The use of game theory and mixed strategies also suggests that cs.GT is a likely sub-category. The paper's focus on improving the quality of generated images suggests that cs.CV is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and optimization techniques suggests that cs.AI and cs.NE are also possible sub-categories.
